{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcea-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5115"},"text":"§ 5115.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Training curriculum for the public sector","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebceb-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In coordination with the Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, the Chairman of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission, the Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency, the Secretaries of Labor, Energy, and Health and Human Services, and the Director of the National Institute of Environmental Health Sciences, and using existing coordinating mechanisms of the National Response Team and, for radioactive material, the Federal Radiological Preparedness Coordinating Committee, the Secretary of Transportation shall maintain, and update periodically, a current curriculum of courses, including online curriculum as appropriate, necessary to train public sector emergency response and preparedness teams in matters relating to the transportation of hazardous material. Only in developing the curriculum, the Secretary of Transportation shall consult with regional response teams established under the national contingency plan established under section 105 of the Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensation, and Liability Act of 1980 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s9605"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 9605","children":[],"tail":"), representatives of commissions established under section 301 of the Emergency Planning and Community Right-To-Know Act of 1986 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11001"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 11001","children":[],"tail":"), persons (including governmental entities) that provide training for responding to accidents and incidents involving the transportation of hazardous material, and representatives of persons that respond to those accidents and incidents."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcec-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Requirements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The curriculum maintained and updated under subsection (a) of this section—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebced-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" shall include—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcee-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a recommended course of study to train public sector employees to respond to an accident or incident involving the transportation of hazardous material and to plan for those responses;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcef-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" recommended courses and minimum number of hours of instruction necessary for public sector employees to be able to respond safely and efficiently to an accident or incident involving the transportation of hazardous material and to plan those responses; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcf0-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/b/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" appropriate emergency response training and planning programs for public sector employees developed with Federal financial assistance, including programs developed with grants made under section 126(g) of the Superfund Amendments and Reauthorization Act of 1986 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s9660a"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 9660a","children":[],"tail":"); and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcf1-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" may include recommendations on material appropriate for use in a recommended course described in clause (1)(B) of this subsection.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcf2-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Training on Complying With Legal Requirements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A recommended course described in subsection (b)(1)(B) of this section shall provide the training necessary for public sector employees to comply with—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcf3-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" regulations related to hazardous waste operations and emergency response contained in part 1910 of title 29, Code of Federal Regulations, prescribed by the Secretary of Labor;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcf4-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" regulations related to worker protection standards for hazardous waste operations contained in part 311 of title 40, Code of Federal Regulations, prescribed by the Administrator; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcf5-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" standards related to emergency response training prescribed by the National Fire Protection Association and such other voluntary consensus standard-setting organizations as the Secretary of Transportation determines appropriate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcf6-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Distribution and Publication","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"With the National Response Team—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcf7-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary shall distribute the curriculum and any updates to the curriculum to the regional response teams and all committees and commissions established under section 301 of the Emergency Planning and Community Right-To-Know Act of 1986 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11001"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 11001","children":[],"tail":"); and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcf8-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s5115/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Secretary may publish and distribute a list of programs and courses maintained and updated under this section and of any programs utilizing such courses.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idca8ebcf9-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272/s1/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-07-05"},"text":"July 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/772"},"text":"108 Stat. 772","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/429/s6/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–429, § 6(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-31"},"text":"Oct. 31, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/4378"},"text":"108 Stat. 4378","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/59/tVII"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–59, title VII","children":[],"tail":", §§ 7113, 7126, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 2005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/1899"},"tex